# @cumulus/lzards-api-client

## Lzards Api Client

The Level Zero and Repositories Data Store (LZARDS) is the "backup of last resort" for 
cloud-native missions and datasets, should the AWS-hosted data become inaccessible for any reason, 
including government policy, breach of contract, financial outage, or catastrophic vendor failure.


## Usage

```js
npm install @cumulus/lzards-api-client
```

## Example
```js
const { submitQueryToLzards } = require('@cumulus/lzards-api-client/lzards');

const now = new Date().getTime();
const thirtyMinutesAgo = now - (1000 * 60 * 30);
const twoMinutesAgo = now - (1000 * 60 * 2);

const searchParams = {
    pageLimit: 25,
    'metadata[provider]': provider,
    'metadata[createdAt][gte]': thirtyMinutesAgo,
    'metadata[createdAt][lte]': twoMinutesAgo,
}

const response = await submitQueryToLzards({ searchParams });
```

